WEBVTT

00:11.042 --> 00:17.010
The scripture for today is the Gospel of Luke, chapter one, verse 26 through 38.

00:18.511 --> 00:20.694
Now please stand for the reading of scripture.

00:26.562 --> 00:29.465
Advent ends in celebration, but it begins in waiting.

00:29.666 --> 00:36.895
So we will stand in unbroken silence, identifying with the plight of the prophets, remembering the redemption we still await.

00:37.536 --> 00:39.378
The redemption our world awaits.

00:39.554 --> 00:43.141
and the God who promises to come again, bringing heaven to earth.

00:44.003 --> 00:46.828
Then the silence will be broken by the reading of Scripture.

00:46.888 --> 00:53.882
The written word breaking silence among us just as the living word broke the long silence with the birth of Jesus.

00:53.942 --> 00:56.146
Now we wait.

01:56.066 --> 02:07.145
In the sixth month of Elizabeth's pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth, a town in Galilee, to a virgin pledged to be married to a man named Joseph, a descendant of David.

02:07.846 --> 02:09.068
The virgin's name was Mary.

02:09.088 --> 02:13.235
The angel went to her and said, Greetings, you who are highly favored.

02:13.816 --> 02:15.058
The Lord is with you.

02:15.874 --> 02:23.602
Mary was greatly troubled at his words and wondered what kind of greeting this might be, but the angel said to her, do not be afraid, Mary, you have found favor with God.

02:24.123 --> 02:27.947
You will conceive and give words to his son and you are to call him Jesus.

02:28.448 --> 02:31.531
He will be great and will be the son of the most high.

02:32.212 --> 02:38.118
The Lord God will give him the throne of his father, David, and he will reign over Jacob's descendants forever.

02:38.459 --> 02:40.060
His kingdom will never end.

02:40.841 --> 02:41.642
How will this be?

02:41.702 --> 02:45.106
Mary asked the angel, since I am a virgin,

02:45.474 --> 02:47.978
The angel answered, the Holy Spirit will come on you.

02:47.998 --> 02:50.662
The power of the most high will overshadow you.

02:50.702 --> 02:54.568
So the holy one to be born would be called the son of God.

02:55.329 --> 02:58.554
Even Elizabeth, your relative, is going to have a child in her old age.

02:59.495 --> 03:03.381
And she who has said to be unable to conceive is in her sixth month.

03:03.942 --> 03:06.065
For no word from God will ever fail.

03:06.085 --> 03:08.809
I am the Lord's servant, Mary answered.

03:09.150 --> 03:10.912
May your word to me be fulfilled.

03:11.553 --> 03:12.555
Then the angel left her.

03:13.556 --> 03:14.738
This is the word of the Lord.

03:15.330 --> 03:16.231
Thanks be to God.

03:20.858 --> 03:24.764
So I'd like to begin this morning with a parable of sorts.

03:25.284 --> 03:32.575
I was flying home with my three boys, just the four of us, the first week of this Advent season.

03:33.496 --> 03:43.250
And we boarded the plane early before the rest of the passengers, like they always call families with young kids, which by the way, just as a brief aside,

03:44.162 --> 03:47.045
That policy makes no sense to me at all.

03:48.006 --> 04:02.443
Everyone boarding the flight is just thinking, I just want to get a spot with my back in the overhead compartment, except parents with young kids who are thinking, I just want to be in this tube constraining my children for as little time as possible.

04:02.864 --> 04:06.308
And then they're like, get in here 30 minutes before everybody else does.

04:06.808 --> 04:08.210
And then you have to watch

04:08.418 --> 04:17.289
The people who have unfortunately been assigned the seat next to you get hit with that realization and the disappointment wash over them while they're boarding.

04:17.990 --> 04:19.131
Someone, anyway.

04:20.633 --> 04:24.658
Amos, my three-year-old, claimed the window seat in our row.

04:24.778 --> 04:27.542
He always wants the window seat.

04:27.842 --> 04:30.285
And this was a cross-country flight.

04:30.325 --> 04:34.490
It was taking off just at dusk on the east coast.

04:34.590 --> 04:37.714
And as we made our sense, the sun was setting.

04:37.922 --> 04:45.293
And Amos has his face pinned against the window going, whoa, look at the sunset.

04:45.914 --> 04:53.926
Can you see that at a volume that is entirely socially unacceptable for an airplane?

04:53.986 --> 04:55.408
And so I'm kind of embarrassed.

04:55.428 --> 05:04.402
I turn to look around at the other passengers to apologize for my son's excitement at the dazzling nature of the sunset outside.

05:04.738 --> 05:08.383
To my utter surprise, no one seems to notice.

05:09.605 --> 05:31.698
Because already, just a few minutes into the flight, everyone else's shade is drawn, and every other face is lit up by a glow, not the glow of the sun that gives light to the world but the glow of an artificial scream by which they are distracting themselves, passing the time until we land in Portland, and it struck me.

05:32.610 --> 05:48.669
Just how quickly in human history we've gone from the miracle of flight to the drag of travel, just closing off the outside world to retreat, pacifying ourselves into some form of entertainment to pass the minutes.

05:48.750 --> 06:02.386
Can you imagine if someone had told the Wright brothers that within a hundred years of when they were wetting themselves in excitement and fear on a beach in North Carolina at Untakeoff,

06:03.010 --> 06:05.915
that everyone else would be yawning and closing the shade.

06:06.876 --> 06:15.069
Can you imagine how much someone would pay for Amos' window seat in Jesus' first-century world?

06:16.210 --> 06:26.226
Or can you imagine if we just announced, hey, we're shutting down the airline industry, how much someone would pay for that seat if this was the last flight in human history?

06:27.554 --> 06:34.363
So there I was sitting at the beginning of another Advent season, Amos attentive to the true light and dazzled by it.

06:34.964 --> 06:42.935
All the rest of us grown too old, too numb, too distracted by our artificial lights to be dazzled by the real thing.

06:44.256 --> 06:57.394
And that, the child on a cross-country flight saying something so simple and so profound to the rest of us, if only we had ears to hear, has everything to do with the enunciation.

06:57.954 --> 07:02.140
That's the fancy title for the scripture that we just read a moment ago.

07:02.160 --> 07:07.208
Annunciation is the English translation of a Latin word for announcement.

07:07.228 --> 07:08.630
It just means announcement.

07:08.711 --> 07:13.438
The announcement of the angel Gabriel to the Virgin Mary goes something like this.

07:13.979 --> 07:21.330
The Holy Spirit will come on you and the power of the Most High will overshadow you so that the Holy one to be born will be called the Son of God.

07:21.474 --> 07:32.488
That announcement has been set apart, highlighted, and titled since early church history because it is among the most loaded statements in the entire Bible.

07:33.049 --> 07:41.120
In fact, the Annunciation is the whole Bible compressed into a single announcement.

07:41.140 --> 07:42.001
Let me show you what I mean.

07:42.762 --> 07:46.066
First, this announcement harkens back to creation.

07:46.530 --> 07:51.519
The Holy Spirit will come on you and the power of the Most High will overshadow you is a biblical cue.

07:51.579 --> 07:54.184
Genesis chapter 1 verse 1.

07:54.845 --> 07:56.848
In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.

07:56.908 --> 07:58.431
Now the earth was formless and empty.

07:58.471 --> 08:04.562
Darkness was over the surface of the deep and the spirit of God was hovering over the waters.

08:05.026 --> 08:14.923
So the opening lines of Jesus' story are meant to draw to mind the opening lines of the whole story, just as the Holy Spirit hovered over the waters of chaos to bring light out of darkness.

08:15.264 --> 08:23.398
So the same Holy Spirit is hovering over this present chaos to bring light out of darkness.

08:24.119 --> 08:27.204
And that's more than just the poetic wink of a seasoned writer.

08:27.244 --> 08:30.450
It's a profound claim about the child in Mary's womb.

08:30.946 --> 08:37.513
The whole reason this announcement begins by harkening back to creation is because creation did not go as planned.

08:38.354 --> 08:42.039
Creation came apart when a fallen angel told a lie.

08:42.559 --> 08:46.323
Did God really say you must not eat from any tree in the garden?

08:46.384 --> 08:55.634
The crafty lie woven by a fallen angel back in Genesis wasn't a lie about forbidden fruit, it was a lie about the love of God.

08:56.226 --> 09:02.896
The serpent questions and critiques Eve's trust in God until he's planted the seed of a lie in her imagination.

09:02.956 --> 09:05.881
Maybe God doesn't know the way to blessing.

09:06.822 --> 09:11.229
Maybe his definition of abundant life isn't as dialed in as yours is.

09:11.649 --> 09:14.454
Maybe he's holding out on you to some degree.

09:14.874 --> 09:24.068
The serpent takes aim at Eve's trust in God until she reaches for the very love that she's already been freely and unconditionally given by her own effort.

09:24.088 --> 09:25.330
And that's what sin is.

09:25.858 --> 09:42.122
It's an attempt to achieve what I've already been given, to become by achievement who I am by grace, to earn the belovedness God freely gave me before I even had a chance to earn it or lose it.

09:43.023 --> 09:50.514
When Eve reached for the forbidden fruit in response to the fallen angels lie, she lost both God's identity and her own.

09:50.914 --> 09:55.632
You see sin is a lie that strips us of our freely given beloved identity.

09:56.114 --> 10:01.554
And so in reaction, Adam and Eve cover up, they clowed themselves in fig leaves, they put it on a preferred

10:01.602 --> 10:12.579
presentable self and the exposure that sin leaves us and we reach and grab for whatever we can to feel whole, to feel beloved in the way that we were at first but lost.

10:12.980 --> 10:16.626
I reach for image or accolades, pleasure, security, whatever.

10:16.686 --> 10:19.971
I just dress myself up and some misguided search for love.

10:20.532 --> 10:24.498
All of that just set off by a lie from my fallen angel.

10:25.506 --> 10:31.594
But the very creation that came apart when a fallen angel told a lie is repaired when a heavenly angel tells the truth.

10:32.435 --> 10:43.388
The Annunciation reaches all the way back to creation to claim that what God is doing in the prayer closet of a rural Palestinian teenager is every bit as profound as what God was doing on the first page of the Bible.

10:43.829 --> 10:48.074
The Annunciation reaches back to creation to make the claim of recreation.

10:48.535 --> 10:51.378
Like I said, it's a loaded statement.

10:53.186 --> 11:00.173
The truth that repairs the lie goes like this, the Holy Spirit will come on you and the power of the Most High will overshadow you.

11:00.773 --> 11:20.071
So the truth being told about God here is that He keeps His promises, keeps them even more personally than anyone dared to imagine, not only Emmanuel God with us, but Emmanuel God within you, Mary, the result of which is, so the Holy one to be born will be called the Son of God.

11:20.572 --> 11:23.154
Now here is why the virgin birth matters.

11:24.066 --> 11:31.614
Because if what is happening to Mary here is just an isolated event, then sure, go ahead and allegorize it if you want.

11:31.934 --> 11:47.691
But if it's the repair of what went wrong, if it's a reversal of the serpent's deception and sins consequences, well, then it must be an independent, creative act of the very same spirit who made the world and me write in good in the first place.

11:48.292 --> 11:50.514
And that's what the angel claims it is.

11:51.234 --> 11:54.078
Second, this announcement fulfills the temple's promise.

11:54.980 --> 12:01.389
So the Holy Spirit will come on, you and the power of the Most High will overshadow you, Gabriel's sestinary.

12:02.050 --> 12:09.441
The dramatic act of deliverance foundational to the New Testament is the incarnation when God came to live among us in Jesus.

12:09.882 --> 12:18.194
The dramatic act of deliverance foundational to the Old Testament is Exodus when God came to live among us in the temple.

12:18.626 --> 12:22.590
In Exodus, God's presence is depicted as a dense cloud.

12:23.511 --> 12:33.880
A cloud guides the Israelites through the wilderness, a cloud descends on Mount Sinai when Moses meets with God face to face, and eventually arriving at where they'd settle.

12:33.900 --> 12:40.046
In the final chapter of the book, God instructs Moses to build a temple where he will come to live among his people.

12:40.467 --> 12:48.274
And when he does, Exodus 40, then the cloud covered the tent of meeting, and the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle.

12:48.482 --> 12:58.695
But the very same chapter also tells us, Moses could not enter the 10th of meeting because the cloud had settled on it and the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle.

12:59.296 --> 13:06.946
Now had settled in the most ancient rabbinical Greek record of Exodus is the word overshadowed.

13:07.707 --> 13:13.394
Moses could not enter the temple because the Holy Spirit overshadowed it.

13:14.146 --> 13:30.449
The Annunciation is reaching back to the temple to pull the temple into the womb of a human being, making the claim that the place gone is replanting Eden, the soil on which he is renewing the world is within an unassuming otherwise unimpressive young girl.

13:31.050 --> 13:34.034
Mary's body is the temple.

13:34.434 --> 13:46.332
The place that is overshadowed by the Holy Spirit, the place where God lives, the very presence of God so potent that Moses who spoke face to face with God like a friend, not even Moses could enter the room.

13:46.672 --> 13:49.456
That very presence is now in your womb, Mary.

13:49.937 --> 13:51.119
That's the announcement.

13:52.601 --> 13:54.504
But this announcement is only reaching back.

13:54.524 --> 13:56.787
The announcement also points forward to the spirit.

13:57.648 --> 14:00.372
Look again with me at Luke chapter one verse 35.

14:01.474 --> 14:04.178
The Holy Spirit will come on you.

14:05.250 --> 14:18.490
Now, of all the gospel writers, all four who gave us a record of Jesus' life, only Luke went on to write a sequel, Acts, which records Jesus' very final post-resurrection appearance to his disciples.

14:19.111 --> 14:27.905
And the very last thing he tells them tells us is, you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes on you.

14:27.945 --> 14:31.410
It's the very identical phrase.

14:32.386 --> 14:35.911
You see, this is Luke's way of claiming that Mary was not a divine exception.

14:35.971 --> 14:37.473
She was the beginning of a new pattern.

14:38.214 --> 14:46.805
The very Holy Spirit who filled Mary with the life of God himself will come to fill you and me and all who called Jesus Lord with the life of God himself.

14:47.326 --> 14:51.552
That means the enunciation is less like a record scratch and more like a key change.

14:52.974 --> 15:02.226
Right, if the Bible's a piece of music, the same melody carries the whole story, but there's a key change with Gabriel's loaded statement, same melody, new octave.

15:02.946 --> 15:07.313
The Annunciation points forward to the Spirit to claim Mary is not a divine exception.

15:07.333 --> 15:09.656
She is the beginning of a new divine rule.

15:09.716 --> 15:16.828
And finally, what I'm getting at is that the announcement makes promise personal.

15:18.831 --> 15:21.715
The Holy Spirit will come on you.

15:21.735 --> 15:28.786
The power of the Most High will overshadow you.

15:30.466 --> 15:38.677
The announcement will grow until the child within your womb, Mary, 33 years later, that you will include the whole world.

15:38.737 --> 15:49.772
But tonight, God's starting with you, my dear, the cosmic fate of the human race is alive within you.

15:49.832 --> 15:54.338
It's not the first time God's made an announcement like this.

15:55.599 --> 15:57.522
Old Testament redemption starts with

15:57.794 --> 16:00.818
when heaven made an announcement to a man named Abraham.

16:01.358 --> 16:10.550
You, though your wife Sarah is old and barren, you will become a father to a nation outnumbering the stars and the sky through which I will rescue and renew all of creation.

16:11.912 --> 16:16.217
All of that through a son that I'm gonna place in Sarah's womb.

16:17.479 --> 16:22.485
And what does Genesis 15 tell us, set Abraham apart from everybody else?

16:24.488 --> 16:26.450
Abram believed the Lord

16:26.882 --> 16:28.767
and he credited him as righteousness.

16:29.589 --> 16:32.076
Now we're going to look into this much more deeply on Christmas Eve.

16:32.096 --> 16:38.011
So for today, I want to simply note that the promise Abraham believed wasn't general.

16:39.435 --> 16:40.498
It was personal.

16:41.730 --> 16:47.542
He wasn't righteous in God's sight because he believed that God created the world or would redeem the human race.

16:47.903 --> 16:56.200
He was righteous because he believed God's very personal promise to him, that God would make him the father of a nation, not numbering the stars.

16:56.521 --> 17:02.994
That God would redeem the human race through a child he would miraculously place in the womb of his wife.

17:04.066 --> 17:09.794
New Testament redemption starts similarly when heaven made a familiar announcement, this time to a woman named Mary.

17:09.914 --> 17:19.688
You, though you are a virgin, will become the mother of a son in the line of Abraham through whom I will fulfill my first and greatest promise to rescue the human race and renew all of creation.

17:20.809 --> 17:24.775
All of that through a child I miraculously put in your womb, Mary.

17:26.617 --> 17:33.106
So did Mary, like Abraham before her, believe God's most sweeping promise could really be this personal?

17:34.306 --> 17:35.908
Luke chapter 1 verse 46.

17:37.170 --> 17:41.636
And Mary said, my soul glorifies the Lord and my spirit rejoices and God my Savior.

17:41.896 --> 17:45.340
For he has been mindful of the humble estate of his servant.

17:45.801 --> 17:51.068
From now on, all generations will call me blessed.

17:51.629 --> 17:56.415
For the mighty one has done great things for me.

17:56.475 --> 17:58.898
Holy is his name.

18:00.098 --> 18:14.394
You see, Mary looked down the barrel of the ancient past, remembering God's creation, his promises to Abraham, his deliverance and exodus, and she realizes the mighty one has done great things for me.

18:15.855 --> 18:25.005
He's been preparing this role since the lie interrupted the story, and he's cast me in it.

18:27.127 --> 18:29.490
It's one thing to believe God's promises to the world,

18:30.498 --> 18:33.662
It's another thing entirely to believe God's promises to me.

18:35.344 --> 18:36.926
That's so much more vulnerable.

18:37.988 --> 18:39.850
It puts so much more skin in the game.

18:39.890 --> 18:42.494
It requires much more courage and much more hope.

18:44.216 --> 18:54.429
Right, it's one thing for you to sit here believing that God provided a child for Sarah and Mary, but it's another thing to believe that he'll provide a child for me after another unsuccessful round of IVF.

18:55.751 --> 18:58.194
Or now that I'm in my 40s and still single,

18:58.946 --> 19:03.258
or after the secret abortion that I still wear around like a cloak of shame.

19:04.903 --> 19:08.012
It's one thing to believe that God still heals the sick.

19:08.052 --> 19:10.098
It's another thing to believe he'll heal me.

19:12.034 --> 19:13.576
And look, don't misunderstand what I'm saying.

19:13.636 --> 19:19.703
God doesn't open the womb of every barren woman or heal the ailment of every diagnosis of every suffering person.

19:19.743 --> 19:20.725
That's not what I'm saying.

19:21.045 --> 19:22.246
Here's what I am saying.

19:22.567 --> 19:29.175
God does make personal promises to each one of his children because he knows us personally, loves us personally, and redeems us personally.

19:29.515 --> 19:31.077
What has God promised you?

19:36.704 --> 19:38.386
And are you struggling to believe him?

19:42.050 --> 19:44.193
It's one thing to believe that God frees the captive.

19:44.233 --> 19:55.191
It's another thing that He will free me of my alcoholism or my narcissism or my consumerism or my workaholism, pick your ism.

19:57.074 --> 20:00.980
It's one thing to believe that God so loved the world that He would send His one and only Son.

20:01.020 --> 20:07.410
It's another thing to believe that He's numbered the hairs on my head and His good thoughts about me outnumber the grains of sand on all the world's beaches.

20:08.706 --> 20:12.894
It's one thing to believe that Jesus is the way to abundant life for the world.

20:12.974 --> 20:26.138
It's another thing to believe that Jesus is guiding me to abundance, that he doesn't only want to teach me and mature me and grow me up, he wants to bless me, to fulfill my desires, to guide me to joy.

20:26.619 --> 20:30.326
Mary didn't believe God generally or cosmically.

20:30.686 --> 20:32.690
She believed God personally.

20:33.666 --> 20:38.351
The fallen angel that lied to Eve didn't challenge her belief in God generally.

20:38.631 --> 20:41.093
He challenged her belief in God personally.

20:41.414 --> 20:47.059
Did God really say, you sure Jesus is taking you to life?

20:48.260 --> 20:49.982
Are you sure he knows the way?

20:50.022 --> 20:54.586
He'd better give him directions, better get reach over and grab the wheel.

20:56.008 --> 21:02.354
The fallen angel lies to you and me just like he lied to Eve back in Eden and we fall for it like she did.

21:03.490 --> 21:06.179
Go ahead and believe in God generally.

21:06.259 --> 21:07.303
What's the harm there?

21:07.323 --> 21:14.386
So long as I keep His promises at a safe distance, so long as they don't get personal.

21:16.034 --> 21:27.888
The Annunciation is a heavenly angel's announcement claiming God's most ancient, most sweeping, most far-reaching promises must be believed personally if they're to be received personally.

21:28.268 --> 21:36.838
A revelation made plain in the words of the angel Gabriel's lips, greetings you who are highly favored.

21:38.700 --> 21:44.146
Another translation made famous by an old hymn is Mary full of grace.

21:45.570 --> 21:49.335
That's what the angel calls Mary with a little bit of a poetic imagination.

21:49.475 --> 21:51.818
Greetings, Mary, full of grace.

21:53.740 --> 22:00.589
It's a fitting title given all that Mary did to earn her decisive role in God's redemption.

22:03.313 --> 22:04.514
What does the text say?

22:04.534 --> 22:11.163
May Mary stand out from all the other potential candidates for the role of God's mother.

22:12.364 --> 22:13.746
What qualified her?

22:14.690 --> 22:15.712
What about her?

22:15.772 --> 22:18.316
Did God find so impressive?

22:18.757 --> 22:22.663
How did she earn his divine favor and blessing and love?

22:23.204 --> 22:23.544
Nothing.

22:26.329 --> 22:32.259
We're not given a syllable about qualification in the Annunciation.

22:34.763 --> 22:36.786
It's just receiving.

22:38.146 --> 22:40.229
She receives the angel's announcement.

22:40.649 --> 22:43.112
She receives the life of God in her womb.

22:43.513 --> 22:45.956
She receives the name heaven knows her by.

22:46.497 --> 22:47.578
Mary, full of grace.

22:47.598 --> 22:49.781
H.A.

22:49.881 --> 22:52.284
Cheryl writes, Mary did not achieve anything.

22:52.304 --> 22:53.726
She received everything.

22:55.929 --> 22:58.713
Recall the deception that unwound creation at the beginning.

22:58.753 --> 23:02.738
Take from God what he's already promised to give you.

23:03.874 --> 23:10.864
The drama of the Old Testament is person after person graced by God and struggling to trust in that grace continually.

23:12.206 --> 23:20.818
Abraham believed God filled with grace, but then Abraham also tried to fulfill God's promise for him by sleeping with a surrogate.

23:22.240 --> 23:23.602
And his son Isaac

23:23.682 --> 23:34.386
carrier of the same grace, child of the promise lies in the face of fear is reluctant to trust God through famine and favors his older brother when God says the promise is with the younger.

23:36.386 --> 23:42.032
And that younger brother, Jacob, he is such a mess that he is named for deception.

23:42.112 --> 23:46.057
And he goes on to father 12 sons who will become Israel's 12 tribes.

23:46.137 --> 23:53.705
It's all a nation of people who God has filled with grace enough to share with the whole world who are struggling to trust that grace continually.

23:54.626 --> 24:01.714
And then an angel interrupted that family lineage to offer a new name to an ordinary woman, Mary full of grace.

24:02.946 --> 24:08.192
She was so full of grace that she carried the personification of grace in her womb.

24:08.513 --> 24:19.406
And when the fallen angel's lie was exposed by the heavenly angel's announcement, Mary recovered both the truth about God that he keeps his promises, that he can be trusted and the truth about herself.

24:19.746 --> 24:22.810
And I am Mary full of grace.

24:26.715 --> 24:32.722
Heaven came down to say to her, Mary, you are not a powerless woman in a patriarchal world.

24:33.186 --> 24:37.756
You are not a rural peasant in a world that is run by metropolitan elites.

24:38.097 --> 24:41.605
You are not a Jewish girl squashed by the Roman aristocracy.

24:41.885 --> 24:43.669
You are very full of grace.

24:46.415 --> 24:48.420
Hear the announcement this morning, friends.

24:49.843 --> 24:53.010
You are not your diploma or your resume.

24:54.114 --> 24:58.558
You are not your last name or your family of origin or your socioeconomic status.

24:58.858 --> 25:04.604
You are not your weight or your waist size or your desirability according to any cultural standard.

25:04.904 --> 25:10.369
You are not your relationship status, your parenting status, your friendship status or your social calendar.

25:10.389 --> 25:13.772
You are not your last year, your last week or your last mistake.

25:14.073 --> 25:15.314
You are full of grace.

25:16.975 --> 25:18.397
You are Richard full of grace.

25:19.017 --> 25:20.599
You are Bethany full of grace.

25:21.039 --> 25:22.481
You are Nate full of grace.

25:22.541 --> 25:23.922
That is who you are.

25:24.994 --> 25:30.921
And the fight of your life is and always will be to trust that grace continually.

25:31.862 --> 25:38.149
To not merely believe God wants, but to trust God continually when he says that to you are.

25:39.571 --> 25:49.042
To know Mary not as one lucky exception, but the first in a long line of grace carrying, grace trusted, grace defined disciples.

25:49.826 --> 25:51.609
It is grace that found you first.

25:52.050 --> 25:53.553
It is grace that renamed you.

25:53.853 --> 25:56.739
Grace that called you, filled you, and redeemed you.

25:57.059 --> 25:59.264
And it is grace that finds you again today.

26:00.386 --> 26:02.590
Grace that reminds you who you really are.

26:02.630 --> 26:05.976
Grace that calls you by the only name that heaven knows you by.

26:06.016 --> 26:07.519
Grace that refills you.

26:07.840 --> 26:13.490
Grace that keeps on reminding you of that till he's washed out every trace of that old lie within you.

26:14.338 --> 26:26.316
as it says in Titus 3, but when the kindness and love of God our Savior appeared, He saved us not because of righteous things we had done, but because of His mercy.

26:27.158 --> 26:42.962
He saved us through the washing of the rebirth and renewal by the Holy Spirit, whom He poured out on us generously through Jesus Christ our Savior so that, having been justified by His grace, we might become heirs, having the hope of eternal life.

26:44.578 --> 26:50.928
Or as Tim Keller summarizes the whole story, the one who made you at the beginning is making you again.

26:52.570 --> 26:53.592
That's the announcement.

26:54.353 --> 26:55.595
It's the enunciations.

26:55.675 --> 26:59.541
The whole Bible compressed into a single statement.

27:01.745 --> 27:12.882
Before that, a flight where little Amos made his personal enunciation to the rest of us passengers on that trip I took with my boys to the east coast, I woke up early one morning

27:14.050 --> 27:18.054
Still dark outside, my kids jetlagged from the trip.

27:18.114 --> 27:21.918
They've probably got hours more that they're going to sleep.

27:22.999 --> 27:28.865
And so I set off on an early morning jog to this nearby arboretum near what we were staying in.

27:29.645 --> 27:31.267
It had snowed the night before.

27:31.307 --> 27:37.653
And so I felt like I was running on two spoons wrapped in banana peels.

27:38.995 --> 27:42.258
But it was magic.

27:43.490 --> 27:50.761
It was like I was inside of a snow globe, just like a winter wonderland in this quiet forest.

27:51.863 --> 27:54.868
It was December 3rd, right at the beginning of the Advent season.

27:54.888 --> 28:00.577
And before I set off, I had read and been struck by these words from Genesis chapter 8.

28:00.897 --> 28:02.941
Then God remembered Noah.

28:04.804 --> 28:08.850
It struck me because over and over again in Scripture were told to remember God, but

28:08.994 --> 28:16.762
Here's God remembering us, and not remembering people generally, but remembering one particular person in the midst of his creation.

28:17.183 --> 28:22.488
What a statement about God's particular personal love.

28:23.750 --> 28:33.900
And so I went on this early morning run in a dark snow globe, and I was just praying again and again, that prayer of the thief on the cross.

28:34.020 --> 28:35.602
Jesus remember me.

28:37.602 --> 28:40.547
Just I don't know, every couple minutes or so would come back to my mind.

28:40.627 --> 28:42.470
I was just using it as an anchor to hold me.

28:42.511 --> 28:43.532
Jesus remember me.

28:43.552 --> 28:49.583
It was an invitation for him to meet me in some personal way that day with his love.

28:50.264 --> 28:51.706
Jesus remember me.

28:53.269 --> 29:03.026
I was entirely alone on my little trail in this arboretum until eventually I passed this couple walking their dog and the woman kind of mean mugged me.

29:03.938 --> 29:08.042
You know, it just like stared at me long and hard for an eerie amount of time.

29:08.122 --> 29:11.365
And so I just thought, yeah, because that didn't feel great.

29:12.947 --> 29:16.530
I must not be allowed to be in here this early or something.

29:16.590 --> 29:17.091
I don't know.

29:17.671 --> 29:19.213
So I keep on going.

29:19.253 --> 29:21.695
And this trail is a pretty small loop.

29:21.775 --> 29:24.257
And so eventually I'm passing them again.

29:24.297 --> 29:27.981
And she gets in the middle of the trail and starts like blocks the way.

29:28.021 --> 29:29.522
And I was like, oh, gosh.

29:30.103 --> 29:33.266
I'm about to get kicked out of a nature preserve.

29:34.754 --> 29:40.860
And she stops me and then proceeds to explain that she's a follower of Jesus.

29:43.563 --> 29:48.768
And she just goes on to speak these words of blessing and identity over me.

29:49.829 --> 29:59.098
And then her and her husband lay their hands on my shoulders and just pray blessing over me in the dark of this early morning on the east coast.

29:59.619 --> 30:03.122
And a fair summary of her words and then their prayers would just be

30:03.266 --> 30:08.272
Tyler full of grace, Tyler full of grace, Tyler full of grace.

30:10.194 --> 30:22.409
And then I jogged off bewildered that I had been remembered by God, reminded of who I am deepest and truest, and thus began my advent journey.

30:23.670 --> 30:25.633
The one who made you first is making you again.

30:25.673 --> 30:30.098
There's this old Advent prophecy in Zechariah 8,

30:30.690 --> 30:35.616
In fact, it was in the electionary just this past week, which is the common prayer book for Christians all around the world.

30:36.297 --> 30:40.002
And it's full of promises that are beyond imagination.

30:40.362 --> 30:44.688
But here's the refrain the chapter returns to after every single one of those promises.

30:45.148 --> 30:46.851
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

30:49.294 --> 30:50.936
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

30:50.956 --> 30:54.500
I'm jealous for you to know you and be known by you.

30:55.522 --> 30:57.244
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

30:57.544 --> 30:58.866
I'll come and live among you.

30:59.490 --> 31:01.274
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

31:01.515 --> 31:02.537
I'll bring you back home.

31:02.577 --> 31:04.802
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

31:04.842 --> 31:05.664
I'll keep you safe.

31:06.386 --> 31:07.910
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

31:07.970 --> 31:08.912
I'll provide for you.

31:08.952 --> 31:11.217
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

31:11.257 --> 31:15.848
I want to fill your cup, serve you seconds, and laugh with you at the table while the kids play outside.

31:15.908 --> 31:18.354
That's my message translation.

31:20.098 --> 31:22.862
It keeps on going and going like that between every line.

31:22.902 --> 31:24.344
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

31:24.444 --> 31:25.866
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

31:25.947 --> 31:27.429
This is what the Lord Almighty says.

31:27.829 --> 31:29.892
And that refrain, it's instructive for us.

31:31.194 --> 31:43.072
Because when we hear the promise of God spoken over us, when we hear what the Lord Almighty says, the words we pray start to sound a lot like the words that spill off the lips of Mary after the angel's announcement.

31:44.073 --> 31:45.575
Look back down at your Bibles with me.

31:45.615 --> 31:47.538
Luke chapter 1 verse 38.

31:48.066 --> 31:50.468
I am the Lord's servant, Mary answered.

31:51.449 --> 31:53.211
May your word to me be fulfilled."

31:56.054 --> 31:58.056
What can we learn from Mary's response?

32:00.058 --> 32:04.342
Well, we can definitely learn that the favor of God does not equal the favor of man.

32:04.402 --> 32:16.754
The favor of mothering God will immediately win Mary social scandal in the village where she lives, legal trouble in the temple where she worships, and relationship trouble with the man that she's

32:16.898 --> 32:17.919
Hoping to Mary.

32:19.721 --> 32:23.484
We also learned that the blessing of God does not equal the blessing of my plan.

32:23.544 --> 32:27.808
Mary's a young woman with her whole life ahead of her.

32:27.928 --> 32:29.650
Surely she's got hopes and dreams.

32:30.931 --> 32:46.386
Mary, Joseph, have 2.5 kids, start a business on the side, move to the city, maybe live overseas for a little bit, have an adventure or two, eventually settle back down near enough to my folks to capitalize on the free babysitting before enough a way that they're not showing up unannounced.

32:47.298 --> 32:56.332
The blessing of carrying God in her womb is a profound interruption to every plan she's ever made.

32:57.974 --> 33:02.541
Whatever Mary's hopes and dreams were, God's blessing is now an obstacle to those dreams.

33:04.263 --> 33:08.029
And for what it's worth, this is how God's favor and blessing have always worked.

33:09.792 --> 33:11.775
Abraham, I want you to look up at these stars.

33:13.397 --> 33:14.839
Try to count them up if you can.

33:14.879 --> 33:16.722
Now listen to me, old man.

33:16.834 --> 33:26.925
I'm going to make you the father of more people than there are stars in the sky, the one whom all redeemed people are going to trace their lineage back to you.

33:26.945 --> 33:28.207
That's not a bad legacy.

33:29.789 --> 33:30.089
Great.

33:30.109 --> 33:31.491
What do you want from me in return?

33:31.511 --> 33:37.297
I want you to leave your hometown, your family, your friends, your job, and all your security and wander off into the wilderness.

33:38.198 --> 33:38.559
Okay.

33:38.839 --> 33:39.480
Where are we going?

33:40.240 --> 33:41.682
I'll tell you once you're on the way.

33:44.866 --> 33:50.796
The blessing of God is not the blessing of your plan, the maximizing of your potential or the exercising of your agency.

33:50.836 --> 33:53.962
It is much, much better than that.

33:55.625 --> 34:01.014
And it costs you the free and willing surrender of all of that.

34:01.034 --> 34:08.146
Of your plan, your potential and the illusion of control that masquerades is needing to know where the story ends before the stories begun.

34:09.410 --> 34:15.679
And I say that not as a challenge to throw out your plan and do the costly thing that God has called you to do.

34:16.099 --> 34:29.458
I say it as an assurance that if for you today darkness lives larger than light or anxiety feels more present than peace or fear is more real than love, it's not because God has given up on you or taken his grace somewhere else.

34:30.882 --> 34:36.050
If in the recent history of your life, you have made a mess of yourself or others.

34:36.410 --> 34:38.133
God's commitment to you hasn't waned.

34:38.373 --> 34:41.138
He's lavishing you in his grace even right now.

34:42.440 --> 34:48.349
Life according to your plan was and never will be leading to life and life to the full anyway.

34:48.769 --> 34:54.318
But there is one who knows the way and he will never leave you nor forsake you ever.

34:56.181 --> 34:57.042
Your life.

34:57.282 --> 35:18.882
will be every bit as much of a complicated mess as Abraham's and Mary's and everyone in between, and it will be just as eternally consequential, cosmically meaningful as those whom all generations would call blessed to the degree that, like your ancient ancestors, you learn to trust his grace.

35:22.065 --> 35:26.930
Grace in the midst of your fear of all that you want to control but can't.

35:28.610 --> 35:35.246
Grace in the midst of all the plans you had that now lie shattered on the floor in front of you.

35:35.266 --> 35:40.498
Grace in the face of all that you found security in that has been swept like a rug out from under you.

35:41.570 --> 36:03.434
The friendship that you lost, the relationship that you lost, the job that you lost, health you lost, money you lost, house you lost, future you lost, grace washing over the mistake you made that haunts you but you can't undo the people that you hurt, the fool that you made of yourself, the shame that you wear, grace that sounds like, where can I go from your spirit, where can I flee from your presence?

36:03.874 --> 36:07.538
If I rise up to the heights you're there and if I make my bed and the depths you're there too.

36:08.994 --> 36:17.346
Grace that fills you, grace that names you, grace that defines you, grace you did not earn and cannot lose, grace you did not catch and cannot outrun.

36:17.706 --> 36:24.175
I say all of that just to remind you that Advent is the celebration of light breaking darkness.

36:26.338 --> 36:31.826
And in the life of Jesus, the most significant events that all happened in the dark.

36:33.986 --> 36:39.313
He was born in the dark, arrested in the dark, died in the dark, and rose in the dark.

36:39.693 --> 36:44.960
Darkness is never welcome, but God is not afraid of the dark.

36:44.980 --> 36:47.203
It seems to be where he gets his best work done.

36:48.745 --> 36:59.518
I'm saying all this just to assure you that trusting God's grace includes uncertainty, confusion, betrayal, pain, doubt, boredom, and the love of God.

37:01.240 --> 37:02.642
Ready to catch you.

37:03.554 --> 37:12.122
every single time you fall, pick back up the broken parts of you that are lying shattered and remake you just like he did at first.

37:13.984 --> 37:18.589
When Mary prayed, I am the Lord's servant, may your word to me be fulfilled.

37:18.629 --> 37:22.432
She was teaching us to pray in Advent with our eyes fixed on Christmas.

37:24.574 --> 37:32.402
She was willfully accepting the darkness that her life was being plunged into and absolutely certain

37:32.930 --> 37:34.732
that light himself would don.

37:36.555 --> 37:47.529
Some three decades after his mom prayed those words at the Annunciation, Jesus would fall to his knees and get the seminy and pray eerily similar words to his mother.

37:48.910 --> 37:54.197
My father, if it's possible, may this cup be taken from me, yet not as I will, but as you will.

37:56.019 --> 37:58.002
Mary embraced darkness for Jesus.

37:59.298 --> 38:03.182
only for Jesus to embrace all the more darkness for Mary and everyone else.

38:05.324 --> 38:06.786
And the same holds for you and me.

38:06.906 --> 38:17.638
Whatever disruption, whatever pain, whatever darkness you may welcome in the name of Jesus, He has given all the more just to remind you of your real name.

38:18.318 --> 38:23.184
Full of grace, full of grace, full of grace, full of grace.

38:25.967 --> 38:29.010
So here's the invitation on these final days of Advent friends.

38:29.314 --> 38:31.836
Go into your inner room.

38:34.259 --> 38:45.470
When Jesus taught us to pray in the sermon on the mountain, he said, but when you pray, go into your room, close the door, and pray to the Father who is unseen, then your Father who sees what is done in secret will reward you.

38:46.971 --> 38:49.994
Now that word room, it's more fully translated inner room.

38:50.094 --> 38:55.720
The inner room of the temple is where God was said to live, where he took up residence.

38:56.740 --> 38:58.322
So what's Jesus saying here?

38:58.978 --> 39:02.862
Is he saying when you pray, find a private place and make sure you close the door?

39:02.922 --> 39:06.605
Probably to some degree, he means that.

39:07.626 --> 39:13.993
Is Jesus saying when you pray, go into that deepest place within you where you bury your pain, your fear, your longing?

39:15.214 --> 39:16.355
Yeah, he's saying that too.

39:16.415 --> 39:25.744
Is Jesus saying when you pray, go into the inner room of your body, the temple where the spirit of the living God himself is dwelling right now by grace?

39:25.784 --> 39:27.826
Yes, he is certainly saying that part.

39:29.154 --> 39:30.776
So here's the invitation, friends.

39:31.396 --> 39:34.460
Go like Mary into your inner room.

39:36.922 --> 39:39.985
Stare these three days into the darkness that you've buried there.

39:41.567 --> 39:47.874
Name it, your fear, your anger, your shame, your pride, your ache.

39:47.954 --> 39:49.596
Be honest with God about it.

39:49.976 --> 39:55.762
And then ask Him to meet you there as you really are naked

39:55.938 --> 40:01.226
and unashamed in his presence with his grace that made you first and is remaking you right now.

40:04.191 --> 40:09.740
So I'm flying home with Amos and the other boys, the first week of this Advent season, just the four of us.

40:10.341 --> 40:11.703
Whoa!

40:12.644 --> 40:14.047
Look at those sunset!

40:17.352 --> 40:21.298
Only the child dazzled by the wonder of the light that shines on all the world.

40:22.178 --> 40:29.228
The rest of us dazzled by distraction, by the artificial glow of our personal lights, preferred to the wonder of the view outside, there I sat.

40:30.731 --> 40:46.314
On a flight at the beginning of another Advent season, surrounded by so many who had grown too old, too numb, too distracted by artificial lights, and one objectively dismissible little one, prophetically pointing all of us to the real view.

40:47.916 --> 40:49.499
Here is the invitation family.

40:50.420 --> 40:51.762
Go into your inner room.

40:53.986 --> 40:55.388
Today is December 21st.

40:55.549 --> 41:00.497
It is the Winter Solstice, the darkest day of the year.

41:03.482 --> 41:14.802
Three days from right now is Christmas Eve, the brightest celebration of the year, the dawning of the true light himself dazzling, all looking out the window into the dark.

41:15.586 --> 41:21.974
all who are not too numb, too distracted, too entertained by the artificial glow to wait on the light of the world.

41:22.334 --> 41:24.377
Do not distract yourself these three days.

41:25.838 --> 41:29.823
Don't pass the hours, the time, the precious days of your one and only life.

41:30.164 --> 41:31.345
Go into your inner room.

41:33.428 --> 41:36.231
Mary embraced the darkness to carry light.

41:38.173 --> 41:39.055
So go do the same.

41:40.917 --> 41:41.938
Face your darkness.

41:44.002 --> 41:51.931
Name it in prayer, ache over it, plunge into it willfully, and as you do, invite the light of the world to meet you there.

41:53.933 --> 41:55.255
But don't give him directions.

41:58.038 --> 41:58.778
Listen to him.

42:01.522 --> 42:07.688
This is what the Lord Almighty says, greetings you who are highly favored.

42:09.370 --> 42:12.754
This is what the Lord Almighty says, the Holy Spirit will come on you

42:13.346 --> 42:15.529
The power of the most high will overshadow you.

42:15.549 --> 42:21.677
This is what the Lord Almighty says, the one who made you at the beginning is making you again.

42:21.717 --> 42:41.123
To live by the grace I'm filled with, I've got to continually hear what the Lord says over me, the name that He calls me by even, or maybe especially, especially when the night around me grows darkest.

42:41.464 --> 42:43.346
So go into your inner room, friends.

42:44.066 --> 42:58.163
Listen, there is great reward for those who are willing to face the life they're living rather than distract themselves from it and face it assured of the grace of God redeeming them.

42:58.183 --> 43:04.230
So one final time, I just offer you a familiar question framed in a new way.

43:05.572 --> 43:10.959
What can I do to make my life 10% more attentive these three days?

43:13.121 --> 43:13.842
Right?

43:14.082 --> 43:19.691
Living in that psychological principle, the growth comes when we're pushed about 10% beyond our current capacity.

43:19.731 --> 43:27.203
So if you want to get stronger and you can currently bench press 100 pounds, you shouldn't try to bench press 200 pounds, that will collapse your sternum.

43:28.765 --> 43:36.658
Instead, try 110, then when you're ready, 120, then maybe 140 in a couple months.

43:37.794 --> 43:47.169
So if you want to grow in attentiveness, you probably don't start with a 72-hour water fast while locking yourself in an actual closet between now and Christmas Eve.

43:49.192 --> 43:53.258
Instead, you probably just reflect on a familiar question in a new way.

43:53.779 --> 43:57.105
What can I do to make my life 10% more attentive these three days?

44:00.510 --> 44:02.072
What distraction could I eliminate?

44:03.795 --> 44:05.618
What entertainment might I resist?

44:07.330 --> 44:09.754
What darkness might I need to face?

44:11.777 --> 44:13.639
What do I need to acknowledge before God?

44:14.661 --> 44:17.746
Or do I need to confess to a trusted companion?

44:18.687 --> 44:36.594
What can I do to make my life 10% more attentive for three days so that the next time I step into this room on Christmas Eve, I am ready to be dazzled by the light himself arriving personally

44:37.026 --> 44:48.137
To me, like he always has, so that the words spilling forth off my lips sound like I am the Lord's servant.

44:48.157 --> 44:49.899
May your word to me be fulfilled.

44:53.842 --> 44:55.064
Holy Spirit, would you come?

45:01.730 --> 45:05.874
Thanks for joining the Bridgetown family as we engage in this teaching series.

45:06.210 --> 45:12.199
To learn more about the life of our church and how you can get involved, visit bridgetown.church slash welcome.

45:12.960 --> 45:21.071
If you're interested in contributing financially to bridgetown church and to our ministry, you can do that at bridgetown.church slash giving.

45:21.833 --> 45:31.186
Wherever you're joining us from, we hope this resource blesses you and encourages you to be with Jesus, become like Jesus, and do what Jesus did.

